    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <head>No. 4.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">McLane</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="*" xml:id="d527fn1">Identic
                                    instructions were sent to the United States ministers to
                                    Germany, Russia, and Sweden and Norway.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-02-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 7,
                                        1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 293.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith, for your
                                information, two printed copies of an instruction<note n="†" xml:id="d527fn2">For this instruction see <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>, No. 8.</note> of this date to E. J. Phelps,
                                esquire, United States minister <pb facs="0868" n="1826" xml:id="pg_1826"/> at London, in response to a dispatch from
                                him, in which it was stated that Lord Salisbury had expressed
                                acquiescence in a proposal made by me for an agreement between the
                                United States and Great Britain in regard to the adoption of
                                concurrent regulations for the preservation of fur seals in Behring
                                Sea from extermination by destruction at improper seasons and by
                                improper methods by the citizens of either country.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F.
                                Bayard</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
